-- DuPont Acquired Verdezyne Sugar-to-Fuels Enzyme Technology
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2012-12-17T16:00:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-17/dupont-acquired-verdezyne-sugar-to-fuels-enzyme-technology.html
DuPont Co., the largest U.S.
chemical maker by market value, bought from Verdezyne Inc. the
rights for an enzyme technology that’s used to convert sugar
into fuel and chemicals.  The patented xylose isomerase technology is used to
metabolize pentose sugar in biomass, closely held Verdezyne,
based in Carlsbad, California, said today in a statement. Terms
of the purchase weren’t disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
